  "prompt": "How has technology changed the education system?",
  "response": "Technology has transformed education in several key ways:\n\n1. Digital Learning\n- Online courses and e-learning platforms\n- Access to educational resources worldwide\n- Interactive learning tools and apps\n\n2. Classroom Technology\n- Smart boards and digital projectors\n- Tablets and laptops for students\n- Digital textbooks and learning materials\n\n3. Communication\n- Virtual classrooms\n- Video conferencing for remote learning\n- Easy collaboration among students and teachers\n\n4. Personalized Learning\n- Adaptive learning software\n- Customized learning paths\n- Individual student progress tracking\n\n5. Research and Information Access\n- Internet research capabilities\n- Digital libraries\n- Instant access to vast information sources\n\n6. Skill Development\n- Coding and digital literacy programs\n- Technology-based skills training\n- Preparation for digital workplace\n\n7. Accessibility\n- Learning opportunities for students with disabilities\n- Remote learning options\n- Global educational resources\n\n8. Assessment and Feedback\n- Online testing\n- Automated grading systems\n- Real-time performance tracking\n\n9. Cost Reduction\n- Decreased textbook expenses\n- More affordable learning resources\n- Reduced infrastructure costs\n\n10. Collaborative Learning\n- Global student interactions\n- Group project platforms\n- Knowledge sharing across geographical boundaries\n\nThese changes have made education more flexible, interactive, and accessible.",
